en_215616_0	Kaththankudy Police said that an empty suicide kit was found from the house of Rilwan Hashim, the brother of Zahran Hashim who masterminded the Easter Sunday bomb attacks.
en_215616_1	Rilwan Hashim’s father-in-law and mother-in-law were also taken into police custody during this raid in their house at Kaththankudi.
en_215616_2	Meanwhile the bodies of 15 persons including the suicide bombers who blew themselves up after exchanging fire with the security forces at Saindamarudu in Kalmune were buried at Ampara cemetery amid high-security today.
en_215616_3	Among the dead were Zahran Hashim’s father, Mohamed Hashim, two brothers, Zaini Hashim and Rilwan Hashim and Rilwan’s wife.
en_215616_4	Meanwhile, Zahran Hashim’s 25-year old sister, Mohammadu Hashim madaniya was also arrested during a search operation in kaththankudi yesterday.
en_215616_5	She possessed 2 million rupees at the time of the arrest and police believe that she received the money from his brother Zahran Hashim.
en_215616_6	Meanwhile, it is reported that Digamadulla UNP MP MIM Mansoor has visited the wife and the child of Zahran Hashim, who are under treatment at Ampara hospital.
en_215616_7	However, Mansoor’s driver was arrested with some explosives and two pistols in his possession during a search operation in Samanthurai yesterday.
en_215616_8	In addition, the Colombo district organizer of Thawheet Jamath organization, Mohamed Farook Mohamed Fawaz has been remanded until May 7th.
en_215616_9	Police believe Mohamed Fawaz is responsible for producing the circuits for the Easter Sunday bombs.
